      "description": "Eight-propagator subtopology FG (5 vertices, 8 internal edges including a double edge between $v_1$-$v_2$) representing the convolution of a two-loop propagator-type integral $F$ and a one-loop propagator-type integral $G$. Obtained by shrinking one line from $H$ or $X$ (setting $n_2=n_{10}=0$ in the auxiliary topology). The reduction strategy splits the integral into $F$ and $G$ parts, applies tensor reduction and generalized dimensional recurrence relations from Tarasov (1997) to each part separately, followed by partial fractioning and recurrence relations for tadpoles with different masses.",
